<HEADLINE> Greece, Bulgaria Agree to Strengthen Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 15 (Xinhua) --Visiting Bulgarian Foreign Minister
Stoyan Stalev and his Greek counterpart Theodoros Pangalos have
agreed in their talks here today to strengthen the bilateral
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Speaking Later at a luncheon attended by Stalev and a number of
Greek businessmen, Pangalos said that the Greek government
attached particular importance to the potential of the Bulgarian
economy and was encouraging Greek businessmen to establish
activities in the neighboring country.
</P>
<P>
He also made sure that Athens would back Sofia's efforts to
join the European Union (EU) and the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Stalev hailed the Greek support for Sofia's bid to
join the two Western organizations as "very important", adding
that his country would participate in the June meeting of Balkan
foreign ministers which is to be held in the northern Greek city
of Thessaloniki.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed the importance for Sofia of matters such as
the conveyance of energy and the upgrading of road networks,
issues on which it was decided to step up cooperation with Greece.
</P>
