<HEADLINE> WFP's First Food Aid to Arrive in Albania on Tuesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The World Food Program
(WFP) has announced that its first emergency food aid shipment is
expected to arrive at the port of Durres, Albania, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a press release today, the WFP said that a Greek cargo ship
carrying about 400 metric tons of food aid left the Italian port
of Trieste on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
It said the food will be distributed to 75,000 needy people in
the capital of Tirana as well as in Shkoder, Durres, Kukes,
Elbassan, Korce, Vlore and Srande. The shipment represents the
first consignment of United Nations food aid to Albania since the
recent civil unrest.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the WFP said it was assessing storage and
distribution mechanisms which will soon allow the implementation
of a larger food aid program for destitute families countryside.
</P>
<P>
The food will be targeted at institutions such as orphanages,
homes for elderly and centers for handicapped as well as at
destitute families affected by the collapse of the social welfare
system, the WFP said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
