<HEADLINE> UN Offers to Help Rebuild Turin's San Giovanni Cathedral </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. Educational,
Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO) on Tuesday offered
to help the government of Italy to rebuild Turin's San Giovanni
Cathedral, gutted in a seven-hour blaze on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"UNESCO offers its full support and technical expertise in
world heritage conservation to the government of Italy to restore
this universal symbol of mankind's faith and creative talent,"
UNESCO Director-General Federico Mayor said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the cathedral could be rebuilt through the effort
and goodwill of all faiths throughout the world.  
