<DOCNO> XIE19970416.0019 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fire Erupted in Mina Ahead of Pilgrimage Peak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 15 (Xinhua) -- About 50 people were killed
in a fire which broke out this morning at pilgrims' camps outside
Mecca, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The fire was reported to have started in the east of King Abdul
Aziz Bridge in the Islamic holy city of Mina in Saudi Arabia this
morning ahead of pilgrimage peak.
</P>
<P>
Official Saudi Press Agency reported that the fire that started
11:45 local time spread to the northern Mina region due to strong
winds. So far no detailed reports of casualties are available.
</P>
<P>
About two million pilgrims, 1.2 million from the Arab and
Islamic world and the rest Saudis and residents in the Kingdom,
were either at Kheif mosque to say praises or stay in Mena to
spend the whole day today.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia announced earlier April 16 would be the climax of
Haj when the pilgrims would march to Mount Arafat, when pilgrims
symbolically stone the devil and slaughter sheep and other
animals.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of health centers have been established in various
areas to provide services to the needed.
</P>
<P>
High-tech fire extinguishing devices were also employed to
automatically and forcefully sprinkle water to cap any fire
possible during the Haj festival.
</P>
<P>
The Haj is one of the five pillars of Islam and every Muslim
who is able and can afford to perform it should do so at least
once in his life time.
</P>
<P>
The fire occurred a day ahead of the Arafat day when the
pilgrims will converge on Mount Arafat at the peak of the
pilgrimage services.  
</P>
</TEXT>
