<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 15 (Xinhua) --Zairean President Mobutu
Sese Seko and rebel leader Laurent Kabila might hold direct talks
in South Africa in the next few days, South African Foreign
Affairs Minister Alfred Nzo said today.
</P>
<P>
Nzo made the remarks in his speech on President Nelson
Mandela's budget vote in the National Assembly in Cape Town.
</P>
<P>
Nzo said South Africa was in constant touch with all the major
role-players in Zaire.
</P>
<P>
