<HEADLINE> Human Rights Resolution on China "Useless," Says France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 15 (Xinhua) -- France today said that the human
rights resolution on China proposed by Denmark at the United Nations
Human Rights Commission in Geneva is "useless"and is a
"hypocrisy."
</P>
<P>
The French government spokesman Alain Lamassoure said that the
resolution to be presented by Denmark this evening in Geneva "is
useless."
</P>
<P>
"For seven years, China has the legal and political means to
prevent the debate from taking place in the United Nations, " said
Lamassoure at a government meeting.
</P>
<P>
He recalled that "to end this hypocrisy," French President
Jacques Chirac proposed at the Euro-Asia Bangkok summit in March
1996 that one "organize dialogue with China on human rights, not in
a spirit of confrontation but in a spirit of cooperation."
</P>
<P>
"That shows that this constructive approach is the one which is
effective in favor of human rights. This approach has been since
then held by a great majority of the international community, and
France will continue in this way, " he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
