<HEADLINE> Rainstorm Renders Thousands Homeless in Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 15 (Xinhua) -- A violent rainstorm hit eastern
Nigeria's Yola City on Monday and rendered thousands of its residents
homeless, the official News Agency of Nigeria reported today.
</P>
<P>
The rainstorm, which lasted about one hour, blew away the roofing
sheets of many houses, uprooted trees and wire poles, causing a total
blackout in the capital of Adamawa State, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Local residents have described the rainstorm as "the work of God"
and prayed that all will be good in the coming rainy season, it added.
