<HEADLINE> Preventive Measures Taken to Ward Off Flooding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- People along Awash River are
making preventive preparations to ward off the danger of flood
before the arrival of the coming rainy season, a report from the
Ethiopian News Agency said today.
</P>
<P>
The Awash River which broke three dams last rainy season
flooded Wonji town causing the displacement of 20,000 residents.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the Wonji sugar factory last month
undertook the reinforcement of a nine-kilometer dam. The Metehara
sugar factory is constructing a 42-kilometer dam.
</P>
<P>
Residents of the Wonji town said they expect to pass the rainy
season without fear because of the reinforcement of the dams.
</P>
