Van-Dunem said here today his newly-installed government of
national unity and reconciliation lists enhancing people's health
and education as top priorities.
</P>
<P>
However, the peace in the country having suffered almost 20
years of war "must be consolidated immediately and completely" so
that the government can be successful in improving the medical,
sanitary and housing conditions for Angolans, he said.
</P>
<P>
On health care, the government, assuming office Friday, will
take measures focusing on restoring health facilities and
pharmaceutical factories, adding new equipment and improving
working conditions for medical staff, he said.
</P>
<P>
