teachers' wages so as to meet the demand of them who now launch
strikes frequently, he said.
</P>
<P>
The teaching conditions will also be improved, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also called for the establishment of nationwide
administration structure as soon as possible and stressed the
need to realize the free movement of people and goods around the
country.
</P>
<P>
He said the opposition National Union for the Total
Independence of Angola (UNITA) would hand over diamond-rich areas
it controls to the government in the near future.
</P>
<P>
Agreement on the issue has been reached between UNITA and the
government recently, he said. 
