<HEADLINE> Iranian Business Delegation Cancels Visit to Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 11 (Xinhua) -- A major Iranian business delegation
has canceled a visit to Germany amid strained relations between
Germany and Iran after a German court verdict last week linking
Teheran to the killings of four Kurdish opposition figures in
Berlin five years ago, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
The scheduled April 21-25 visit by the Iranian group of 26
representatives of various industrial sectors was "postponed", the
German Council of Trade and Industry (DIHT), which had invited the
delegation to Germany, said in a statement. No new date had been
proposed by the Iranian side.
</P>
