<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa, Cuba Sign Education Cooperation Pact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 15 (Xinhua) -- South Africa and Cuba have
signed a bilateral framework agreement on education cooperation,
Education Minister Sibusiso Bengu announced today in Cape Town.
</P>
<P>
In a statement following his visit to Cuba, Bengu said the
possible educational cooperation between South Africa and Cuba
should not be clouded by ideological prejudices against the
Caribbean nation.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was a declaration of South Africa's intention to
cooperate with Cuba in the development of their educational
systems, said Bengu.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Cubans may be invited to South Africa to
help teach mathematics, natural sciences and agronomy.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation among high education institutions, on the exchange
of experts in various fields and on setting up joint ventures on
the study of various educational aspects has been stressed in the
agreement, he said.
</P>
<P>
A high-profile Cuban delegation would visit South Africa in
June to consult with various experts and eduz]lnal
practitioners to see the country's needs and capabilities, and
the scope for possible cooperation, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
