<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia to Attend Arushu Summit on Burundi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Zambian President Frederick
Chiluba said here today his country will join in the efforts of
other African countries to find a peaceful solution to the
Burundi problem.
</P>
<P>
He made the statement upon his departure to Arusha, northern
Tanzania, to attend a one-day Great Lakes regional summit on
Burundi on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He said the sanctions against Burundi has more impacts on the
Burundi people.
</P>
<P>
The Burundi people have made various appeals for the sanctions
to be lifted, said the president.
</P>
<P>
Apart from Burundi military leader Pierre Buyoya and rebels,
leaders from Kenya, Uganda, Rwanda, Tanzania, Ethiopia as well as
the Organization of African Unity (OAU) will attend the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Some African countries imposed the sanctions against Burundi
after Buyoya overthrew elected President Sylvestre Ntibantunganya
in a military coup in July last year.
</P>
<P>
The summit will decide whether to tighten or lift the
sanctions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
