<DOCNO> XIE19970416.0065 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambian Minister Urges Police to Build Mortuaries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Zambian health minister Katele
Kalumba called on the police of the country to build its own
mortuaries as soon as possible to keep unclaimed bodies.
</P>
<P>
He said that his ministry has no money to pay for unclaimed
bodies.
</P>
<P>
Local report has said that over 145 unclaimed bodies are
decomposing at the University Teaching Hospital (UTH) mortuary
because of delays by police to conclude investigations.
</P>
<P>
The stench smell from the UTH mortuary has riled residents
nearby, according to Zambia Daily Mail.
</P>
<P>
UTH, the country's biggest hospital, has not cleaned the old
mortuary as a result of unclaimed bodies, most of which are
police cases, UTH assistant spokesperson Pauline Mbangweta,
said.
</P>
<P>
The fridges with a capacity of 63 are unable to cope with the
overcrowding.
</P>
<P>
A fridge meant to take one body is now overloaded with three
to four bodies and these have been there for about five to seven
months due to long police investigations.
</P>
<P>
Police spokesman Standwell Lungu said most of them are
accident victims and there is not much the police could do but
carry out investigations before bodies could be buried. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970416.0066 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Europe-US Arms Sale Race Undermines NATO's Cooperation  in Fighting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The ability of cooperation in
fighting of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) is
threatened by arms sale competition between the alliance's
European members and the U.S., said the latest issue of Defense
Weekly.
</P>
<P>
"Ferocious competition between Europe and the U.S. for arms
sales on world markets threatens to undermine the military
foundation of the alliance, the ability of NATO's 16 member
nations to fight together with compatible weaponry," the report
said.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted senior NATO officials as saying that the
growing trans-Atlantic rift led to fears that the alliance's
integrated military command will be weakened in combat by weapon
incompatibilities.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that arguments about the sharing of industrial
benefits still are hampering the implementation of an integrated
Air Command and Control System of NATO.
</P>
<P>
"While trans-Atlantic defense cooperation is stalled, Europe
is progressing with efforts to consolidate the European defense
market and bolster its defense role," the report said.
</P>
<P>
The 15-member European Union (EU) is making efforts to create a
common foreign and security policy under the union's constitution.
EU governments are also expected to open talks on building a
common defense policy five to seven years later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
