<BODY>
<HEADLINE> International Anti-drugs Conference Opens in Moscow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 16 (Xinhua) -- An international conference to
help bring Russia into the global fight against drugs started in
Moscow today, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the two-day conference, attended by representatives
from more than 20 countries, is to secure international help to
strengthen Russia's ability to fight drug trafficking and
integrate its law enforcement and health service structures with
those of international anti-drugs agencies.
</P>
<P>
Alexander Khodakov, director of the Legal Department of the
Russian Foreign Ministry told reporters Tuesday that the growth of
drug trafficking and use of narcotics in Russia has become a
serious social problem.
</P>
<P>
More than 4 million Russians have experimented with drug-taking
and the number of registered drug addicts has risen to 300,000 in
a country with a population of about 148 million, Khodakov said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
