<HEADLINE> Greece to Set up Special Police Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Greece would set up a special
police force in an effort to stop illegal immigrants from entering
the country, Prime Minister Costas Simitis announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after visiting the Public Order Ministry,
Simitis expressed the hope that the special police force, whose
task would be to guard Greece's borders, would begin operation in
early 1998.
</P>
<P>
In order to increase the manpower available for duties with new
services being set up or the reinforcement of existing
departments, Simitis said, efforts would be made to release
officers from non-policing duties such as serving court documents
and guarding low-risk targets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
