<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Host World Short-Course Swimming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong has won its bid to
host the Fourth World Short-course Swimming Championships in 1999,
 is was announced here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In a written statement issued, A. de O. Sales, president of the
Hong Kong Amateur Swimming Association (HKASA), described it as a
"significant achievement for Hong Kong."
</P>
<P>
"The swimming world will be competing here. The first time
that the World Championships of a major Olympic sport will be
hosted in Hong Kong," he said.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong has hosted many Asian and regional swimming
competitions. "It (HKASA) took a decisive step forward when it
organized in Hong Kong the Swimming World Cup in 1994 and has done
so every year in January since then," said Sales, who is also
chief of Hong Kong's Amateur Sports Federation and Olympic
Committee. 
</P>
