<HEADLINE> Brazilian President to Visit Canada Next Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian President Fernando
Henrique Cardoso will pay a state visit to Canada from April 21 to
24, Canadian Prime Minister Jean Chretien announced today.
</P>
<P>
During the four-day visit, the two sides are expected to
discuss a number of issues, including increased trade and
investment, UN reform, and greater hemispheric integration leading
up to the 1998 Summit of the Americas.
</P>
<P>
"Brazil is our largest export market in South America, and an
increasingly important global actor," Chretien said.
</P>
<P>
"This visit is an important opportunity to broaden our economic
relations, and to advance our partnership on a variety of regional
and international issues," he added.
</P>
<P>
Cardoso will be accompanied by a delegation of Brazilian
ministers and business people.
</P>
<P>
Apart from Ottawa, the president will also visit Toronto and
Montreal, the leading Canadian economic and cultural centers.
</P>
