<DOCNO> XIE19970416.0077 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada's Housing Sales Drop in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Housing sales in Canada dropped
15.7 percent in March after a big jump in the previous month,
reports said today.
</P>
<P>
Figures from the Canadian Real Estate Association indicated
that 17,802 homes traded hands in March, compared with 21,105 in
February.
</P>
<P>
Canadian home buyers slowed their spending after several major
lenders raised mortgage rates in the month.
</P>
<P>
The downturn in March follows a 26-percent rise in housing
resales in February.
</P>
<P>
In March, the average housing sale price across the country
edged up 1.2 percent to 116,840 U.S. dollars, compared with the
same month last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, new sale listings fell 10.2 percent to 39,403, the
reports said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
