<HEADLINE> Moya Wins in Barcelona Open Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Carlos Moya showed his clay-court
ability with an impressive victory over Francisco Clavet Wednesday
at the Barcelona Open tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Open finalist outplayed his fellow Spaniard with
an identical 6-4, which avenged his surprising loss to Clavet last
week in Estoril.
</P>
<P>
Clavet, the losing finalist in Estoril, failed to take his only
opportunity after breaking Moya early in the second set.
</P>
<P>
The Spanish number one took consecutive breaks with several
outstanding lobs and drop shots into the baseline.
</P>
<P>
Moya, still smarting from the Estoril defeat and Spain's
surprise Davis Cup elimination by Italy, said that the victory
helped him to find back some confidence.
</P>
<P>
In the other matches of the day, Andrei Medvedev of Ukraine
beat another Spaniard Carlos Costa 6-2, 6-0.
</P>
<P>
Local favourites Felix Mantilla and Alberto Berasategui set up
a quarter-final encounter after straight-sets wins. 
</P>
</TEXT>
