<HEADLINE> Wuhan Airport Opens to Overseas Aircraft </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The Tianhe Airport in Wuhan, the
capital of central China's Hubei Province, opened to overseas
aircraft today.
</P>
<P>
Since becoming operational after the first-phase construction
was completed two years ago, the airport is now capable of
handling 4.2 million passengers, and 33,000 tons of cargo a
year, or 40,000 landings and take-offs.
</P>
<P>
With a 3,400-m-long, 60-m-wide main runway that allows Boeing
747-400 with a full load to take off, the airport has opened over
50 routes to 45 cities and regions.
</P>
<P>
Having moved from the Nanhu Airport to Tianhe, the Wuhan
Airport opened to planes from Hong Kong ten years ago, with the
number of flights increasing from one to seven a week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
