<HEADLINE>   Chirac Expresses Sorrow Over Mecca Fire Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 16 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
today expressed his condolences over the deaths of 250 pilgrims in
a fire which swept through a camp near the holy city of Mecca in
Saudi Arabia on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a message to Saudi Arabia's King Fahd, Chirac said, "It is
with a great sadness that I learned the tragedy which struck the
kingdom and the whole Muslim community in the sacred period of
pilgrimage."
</P>
<P>
Chirac also expressed his sympathy to the families of the
victims "under these very sorrowful circumstances."
</P>
<P>
Some 2,000 people were also injured in the fire which burned
down hundreds of tents at a camp for pilgrims from India, Pakistan,
Malaysia and Indonesia who had come for the annual haj pilgrimmage
in Mecca.
</P>
<P>
The fire was reportedly caused by a gas bottle explosion. 
