<HEADLINE> PATA 97 Travel Mart Opened in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Over 1,500 representatives from
travel agencies, airlines, hotels, and government tourism
departments of over 40 countries and regions gathered in Beijing
to attend an international travel fair which opened today.
</P>
<P>
The four-day 97 Travel Mart of the Pacific Asia Travel
Association (PATA), the first of its kind held in China, offers
456 booths covering 10,000 square meters in China World Trade
Center. There are 61 booths for China.
</P>
<P>
Sources say the PATA fair is very practical in nature and
offers a good chance for business. Instead of stressing promotion
as in many other travel shows, the PATA fair pre-arranges buyers
and sellers to meet so as they can strike deals right on the spot.
</P>
<P>
Today's travel mart is only one of the three PATA annual events
to take place in China. The PATA Chapters Conference opened today
in Shanghai, and the PATA Annual Conference will be convened in
Beijing on April 20.
</P>
<P>
"The three PATA events will push the on-going Visit China 97 to
new climaxes", said He Guangwei, Chairman of China National
Tourism Administration (CNTA), at today's opening ceremony for the
fair.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1952 and headquartered in San Francisco, PATA is an
influential non-governmental tourism organization, which plays an
important role in the development, promotion, training, and
cooperation in the field of tourism.
</P>
<P>
CNTA joined PATA in 1993, followed by 35 Chinese tourism
bureaus, travel agencies, airlines, and hotels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
