<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine military today
agreed to reposition its force and the Moro Islamic Liberation
Front (MILF) guerrillas in the southern province of Maguindanao to
ease the tension there, the country's military chief said.
</P>
<P>
But meanwhile, Arnulfo Acedera, chief of staff of the
Philippine Armed Forces, said he rejected the MILF's demand for
the total pullout of government troops as a precondition for a
peace agreement between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Instead, he said more government troops will be deployed in the
area if necessary to maintain peace and order and protect the
people in Maguindanao.
</P>
<P>
