recently suggested the repositioning of both the government and
MILF forces in Maguindanao as demanded by the MILF for its return
to the negotiating table.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the MILF called on the government troops to stay away
from their present position and return to their original
positions, which they held before a clash between the two sides in
March.
</P>
<P>
The MILF and the government will resume low-level peace talks
on April 23-25.
</P>
<P>
The MILF, a breakaway faction of the mainstream Moro National
Liberation Front, is currently the largest anti-government force
in the country, with an estimated membership of 12,000.  
</P>
