<HEADLINE> Good Arrangements for Demobilized Soldiers Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The general offices of the State
Council and the Central Military Commission (CMC) asked local
governments to earnestly help settle ex-servicemen and retired
officers.
</P>
<P>
The two offices called on local governments to implement a
circular about demobilization of officers issued by the Leading
Group for Settling Ex-Servicemen and Retired Officers under the
State Council, Organization Department of the Central Committee of
the Communist Party of China (CPC), Ministry of Personnel,
Ministry of Labor, and the General Political Department of the
People's Liberation Army (PLA).
</P>
<P>
The circular said that retired officers will be assigned
civilian jobs according to the government plan this year. The
focus of this year's demobilization will be on retired officers at
the regimental and division levels.
</P>
<P>
Preference will be given to those who have won at least Merit
Citation Class II, those who became handicapped on duty, those who
served in remote areas and areas where natural conditions are
harsh, and those who served on aircraft or naval vessels.
</P>
<P>
The circular asked local governments to guarantee the
legitimate rights and interests of retired officers and their
families who transfer to civilian factories.
</P>
<P>
Training and housing should also be provided for retired
officers.
</P>
<P>
No government departments, mass organizations or enterprises
may refuse to accept retired officers.
</P>
<P>
The circular also encouraged retired officers to work in the
areas that need them most and to make greater contributions to the
country's modernization drive.  
</P>
</TEXT>
