<HEADLINE> 45 Kilograms of Hashish Seized in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The Turkish police have seized 45
kilograms of hashish in an anti-drug operation in eastern
Turkey bordering Iran, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that through a tip-off, the police
searched a house in Cevdet Pasa district of Van province and
found the hashish in 45 parcels within two large bags, which were
brought from Yuksekova town of Hakkari province linking both Iran
and northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The police have taken under custody one suspected smuggler
in connection with the drug trafficking, said the agency.
However, the report failed to give the date when the drugs were
seized.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the Turkish police seized 4.4 tonnes of heroin, which
accounts for 40 percent of the world's total haul, 12.3
tonnes of hashish, 233 kilograms of opium, 13 kilograms of
cocaine and 1,157 kilograms of base morphine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
