<HEADLINE> India's Infrastructure Registers Slow Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The average growth rate of
India's seven critical infrastructure industries grew only by 3.6
percent during the first nine months of the current fiscal year
(April 1996 - March 1997) compared with the 8.3 percent a year
earlier.
</P>
<P>
According to the annual report of the Indian Finance Ministry
available here today, the seven critical infrastructure industries
include electricity, coal, steel, crude oil, refined oil products,
cement and fertilizers, which make up a combined weight of about
31 percent in the index of industrial production.
</P>
<P>
The report said the slowdown in infrastructure industry growth
was mainly due to a decline in crude oil production and power
generation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
