<DOCNO> XIE19970416.0112 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-16 12:51 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> All EU Ambassadors Recalled from Tehran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 16 (Xinhua) -- All ambassadors of the European
Union (EU) member nations have been recalled from Tehran in a
protest against the alleged involvement of Iranian leaders in
murdering Kurdish dissidents, a European diplomat said here today.
</P>
<P>
The diplomat said on condition of anonymity that even Greek
Ambassador Dimitri Tsikouris had left here this morning for
Brussels to participate the special meeting to examine relations
between the EU and Iran.
</P>
<P>
He told Xinhua in a telephone interview that the EU member
states will start a meeting Thursday with all ambassadors
present.
</P>
<P>
"You can interpret the trip by the Greek ambassador whatever
you like," he replied on a question whether the Greek ambassador
was "recalled" or not for the "consultation."
</P>
<P>
However, he said, he was not sure how long it will take for
these ambassadors to come back after the consultation. "That is
the decision to be made at the EU ministerial meeting at Brussels
due on April 29."
</P>
<P>
German Ambassador Horst Beshma was the first to leave from
Tehran after the call from Bonn. Italian Ambassador Ludovico
Ortona left for Rome early this morning.
</P>
<P>
Three non-EU ambassadors from Australia, Canada and New Zealand
have also been recalled back to their home countries.
</P>
<P>
However, Ambassador of New Zealand John Hayes had returned to
Tehran late last night, but he left for Dubai, UAE, this
morning. The Embassy of New Zealand said that he would come back
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian government announced on April 12 that it has
decided to stop purchasing meat, butter and wool from New Zealand
due to Wellington's negative response.
</P>
<P>
Observers here noted that the recalling of ambassadors means a
big backward in Iran's relations with EU countries though they do
not officially downgrade their diplomatic ties from ambassador
level to the level of charge d'affaires.
</P>
<P>
The EU political measure has frustrated Iran's efforts to fight
against isolation and embargo by the United States. Nevertheless,
EU's reaction has been within the political and diplomatic
area. It is believed that They are not going to impose economic
sanctions under the pressure from the Clinton administration.
</P>
<P>
In a response to the EU's political action, the Iranian
government declared that it will recall its ambassadors as a
tit-for-tat measure against European countries.
</P>
<P>
The Berlin high court in its verdict on April 10 accused
Iranian leadership of ordering the assassination of four exiled
Kurdish opposition leaders in Mykono restaurant in Berlin in
1992. The move triggered the diplomatic row between Germany and
Iran. It will also greatly affect economic and trade relations
between Iran and EU member states, which take a share of 41.3
percent of total imports and 32.8 percent of the total exports of
Iran. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
