<HEADLINE> China Takes Firm Measures to Relieve Farmers' Burdens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- China will take tough measures to
punish local government officials who impose heavy financial
burdens on farmers, according to the central authorities.
</P>
<P>
Heavy financial burdens imposed on farmers have become a
prominent problem affecting the country's rural reform,
development, and stability, according to a circular issued jointly
by the Central Commission for Discipline Inspection of the Chinese
Communist Party and the Ministry of Supervision.
</P>
<P>
A nationwide inspection of the work to reduce farmers'
burdens will be carried out by the Party and the government
disciplinary inspection and supervision organizations at all
levels, according to the document.
</P>
<P>
"Any leads to cases involving the imposition of financial
burdens on farmers will be investigated and dealt with," the
document said.
</P>
<P>
"Leading local goverment officials will be blamed if severe
cases of imposing heavy burdens on farmers are discovered in that
region," the document warned.
</P>
<P>
"An inspection and supervision mechanism must be established
and improved with farmers serving as supervisors, liaison workers,
and information collectors in these efforts," it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
