<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice Premiers Listen to Lecture on Taxation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese vice premiers Zhu Rongji,
Li Lanqing, and Jiang Chunyun listened to a lecture on taxation
this morning in Zhongnanhai, site of central government.
</P>
<P>
Gao Peiyong, a professor with the People's University of China,
gave the lecture on taxation theory under socialist market
economy, the major problems in taxation and choice of policies in
the future.
</P>
<P>
After listening to the lecture, Vice Premier Zhu Rongji called
for concerned officials and scholars to study on practical ways to
improve the taxation system.
</P>
<P>
State councillors Li Tieying, Song Jian, Chen Junsheng, and
other officials from the central government attended the lecture.
</P>
<P>
The lecture was part of activities in April to publicize tax
knowledge and increase people's awareness of paying taxes
honestly. Such activities have been conducted every April in the
past five years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
