<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rise On Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Share prices reversed their
downward trend and rose on the Singapore market as the benchmark
Straits Times Industrials Index gained 7.22 points to close at
2,040.19 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 189.2 million units,
valued at 370.56 million Singapore dollars (about 257.33 million
US dollars). Advances overtook declines by 213 to 104, while 296
other counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
MMI was the most actively traded stock as it posted a turnover
of 22.14 million units. It was followed by Westmont Land which had
11.45 million shares traded. The Kuala Lumpur Ind. was next with
9.03 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 led the gainers of the day as it rose by 80 cents
to finish at 18.5 Singapore dollars. NBT gained 60 cents to end at
11.6 Singapore dollars, while the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH)
Foreign picked up by 50 cents to close at 27.2 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, CMB Asia and MISC Foreign shared the top spot
on the losers' list as each of them declined by 16 cents to end at
3.24 and 2.94 Singapore dollars. The Singapore Land fell by 15
cents to close at 6.85 Singapore dollars, while HPL CB warrant 97
finished 12 cents lower at 0.33 Singapore dollar.  
</P>
</TEXT>
