<HEADLINE> China Voices Resolute Opposition to US F-16 Sales To Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- China has urged the United States
to promptly correct its wrongful decision to provide Taiwan with
F-16 fighter jets, Foreign Ministry Spokesman Shen Guofang said
today.
</P>
<P>
Shen said this follows a decision made by the United States in
1992 about the jet sale, in complete disregard of the opposition
of the Chinese government and the Chinese people, decided to sell
150 F-16 fighter jets to Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The move, in direct violation of the August 17 Joint Communique
of the two countries, interferes with China's internal affairs and
has seriously impaired the great cause of the Chinese people for
the peaceful reunification of the motherland, and brought grave
harm to Sino-US relations as well, he said.
</P>
<P>
In noting that the Chinese government lodged a strong protest
with the US side on the issue, he said that today the US insists
on carrying out its wrongful decision in spite of protests and
representations by the Chinese side, which is again expressing its
utmost indignation and resolute opposition to this and has already
made stern representations to the US on this matter.
</P>
<P>
"We demand that the United States immediately adopt effective
measures to correct its wrongful decision on selling F-16 fighter
aircraft to Taiwan and that it return to the right track of
conforming to the three Sino-US joint declarations so as to avoid
causing fresh damage to the Sino-US relations," Spokesman Shen
Guofang said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
