<HEADLINE> Olympiakos' Gray Tests Positive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Olympiakos' American guard Evric
Gray has tested positive for the banned substance ephedrine and
could miss Europe's Final Four Basketball Championship next week,
club officials announced on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Dusan Ivkovic, Olympicakos's Serb coach, revealed the player's
first sample.
</P>
<P>
Gray usually plays as a substitute for team captain George
Sigalas. If he tests positive a second time he faces a three-month
ban by FIBA, the world basketball governing body.
</P>
<P>
Gray, who signed for Olympiakos this season, was tested by FIBA
officials this month before a EuroLeague quarter-final clash with
fellow Greek club Panathiniakos.
</P>
<P>
Olympiakos, finalists in 1994 and 1995, are considered the
favourite along with Spain's Barcelona for this year's crown. The
championship is in Rome from April 22-24. 
</P>
