<HEADLINE> Island to Build Two Rail Links to Mainland (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, April 16 (Xinhua) -- South China's island province of
Hainan plans to build two rail links across the Qiongzhou Strait
to connect it with neighboring Guangdong Province and Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region to the north.
</P>
<P>
The new railway lines, including ferry facilities across the
33-km strait, are expected to ease the pressure on strained
transport services between the island and the mainland, according
to local officials.
</P>
<P>
Due to the lack of rail links, Hainan, a main vegetable
provider in winter, transports most of its vegetables by road,
which costs much more than rail transport, the officials explained.
</P>
<P>
The cost difference in 1995 was estimated at 320 million yuan,
and will reach 1.6 to 1.8 billion yuan by 2000, they said, adding
that the development of several large industrial projects in
Hainan also increased the demand on rail links between the island
and the mainland.
</P>
<P>
A rail line between Hainan and Guangdong, including a section
from Maoming in southwest Guangdong to Hai'an at the seaside, a
ferry between Hai'an and Haikou in Hainan, and a section between
Haikou and Chahe, was approved by the central government in 1993.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 million yuan have so far been invested in the
five-billion yuan project, which is jointly undertaken by the two
provinces and the Ministry of Railways. However, construction of
the Hainan-Guangdong rail link has been slowed down due to a
shortage of funding.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970416.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Island to Build Two Rail Links to Mainland (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hainan therefore plans to build another rail link between
Hainan and Guangxi first, which is estimated to cost only 1.78
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Another advantage of the Hainan-Guangxi link is that the
recently-opened Nanning-Kunming railway provides a main rail
passage to the vast southwest region, which includes Guangxi and
the two provinces of Yunnan and Guizhou.
</P>
<P>
The Hainan-Guangxi line is designed to include a ferry between
Qinzhou, a coastal port in Guangxi, and Yangpu in Haikou, and a
section from Yangpu down to Sanya, the southernmost city in China.
</P>
<P>
Hainan is expected to have a passenger volume of 830.74 million
and a cargo volume of 376.39 million tons by the year 2010, which
will provide enough demand for the two rail links, according to
experts from the No. 4 Surveying and Designing Institute under the
Ministry of Railways.
</P>
<P>
They said the eastern Hainan-Guangdong railway mainly will
carry passengers, while the western Hainan-Guangxi will handle
cargo transport. Central and provincial authorities will be the
chief investors in the Hainan-Guangdong rail link, and local
authorities and enterprises will operate the Hainan-Guangxi line.
</P>
<P>
A feasibility report on the Hainan-Guangxi railway has been
completed by the institute, and some domestic and overseas
businesses interested in the construction of the new railway have
approached authorities in the two provinces.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
