<HEADLINE> EU, Jordan Reach Association Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VALLETTA, MALTA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU)
and Jordan today initialed an association agreement under the
European-Mediterranean partnership scheme.
</P>
<P>
This brings to eight the total number of countries with which
the EU has reached such bilateral accords.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached during the on-going second
European-Mediterranean conference here which is attended by
foreign ministers from the 15 EU members and their 12
Mediterranean neighbors.
</P>
<P>
The first Barcelona conference of the type held in November
1995 set up a goal to establish a free trade zone involving the
two regions -- through reaching bilateral accords.
</P>
<P>
The EU has such accords with Cyprus, Malta, Turkey, Tunisia,
Israel and Morocco, as well as an interim one with the Palestine
National Authority, while negotiating with Egypt, Lebanon and
Algeria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
