<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close With Strong Gains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The Australian share market
posted strong gains today and was hoisted higher by rises in
leading industrials and resources.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index closed 24.7 points, or 1.04 percent,
stronger at 2,406.4, its highest close since March 27.
</P>
<P>
"We are still following the Americans, but we are doing so very
cautiously," broker Peter Struk said.
</P>
<P>
In New York, the Dow Jones industrial average rose 135.26
points, as a report on inflation helped ease some interest rates
fears.
</P>
<P>
Locally, the all industrials index jumped 44.4 points to
3,789.8, while the all resources posted an 8.8 points rise to
1,339.0.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 311.57 million shares worth 869.86
million Australian dollars (674 million US dollars).  
