<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Efforts to Continue to Aid Tibet Called for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, a top leader of the
Chinese Communist Party, has urged other provinces and regions to
continue to aid the development of the Tibet Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Li, a Standing Committee member of Political Bureau of the
Party Central Committee, said today that this is the basis of
various work projects in Tibet, and that "expanding Tibet's
economy is not a mere economic issue, but a great political issue
that has a vital bearing on Tibet's social stability and progress."
</P>
<P>
Addressing a two-day meeting on economic assistance to Tiber
which ended here today, he pointed out that this work is related
directly to the struggle against the Dalai Lama's splittist
attempts and against international anti-Chinese forces, and an
issue on safeguarding China's unification.
</P>
<P>
For the past several years, the central government, provinces,
and regions, especially economically-prosperous coastal ones, have
launched campaigns to provide economic, scientific and cultural
support for Tibet.
</P>
<P>
Li, also chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference, praised these selfless
efforts, and said they have helped forge closeer links
between Tibet and other regions and central government departments.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, a Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau
of the Party Central Committee, met with delegates to the
meeting. 
