<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Schedules Year's Third Treasury Bond Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- China will issue another 40
billion yuan (about 4.8 billion US dollars) worth of treasury
bonds next month, the Ministry of Finance announced today.
</P>
<P>
This third issue of the year is scheduled for May 1-31. The
three-year unregistered bonds will carry an annual coupon rate of
9.18 percent and will be in 100-yuan, 1,000-yuan, and 5,000-yuan
amounts, the ministry said. They can be traded immediately after
the issue closes.
</P>
<P>
In another development, the People's Bank of China, the central
bank, said today that 54.7 billion yuan worth of certificate bonds
have been sold nationwide since March 1, about 44.9 percent of the
planned amount of 123 billion yuan worth.
</P>
<P>
China's annual treasury bond issue has grown rapidly in recent
years, to more than 195 billion yuan last year. Government bonds
this year are budgeted at 248.5 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The first group of treasury bonds, valued at 20 billion yuan,
were issued between January 22 and February 17, and the second
issue of government bonds totaling 123 billion yuan in certificate
bonds started in March and will end on October 20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
