<HEADLINE> Kenya to Hold Trade Exhibition in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Kenya is scheduled to hold a
trade exhibition in Ethiopia in June this year to tap the
unexploited Horn of Africa markets.
</P>
<P>
In a press release, the Network Business Promotion (NBP),
organizer of the fair, said that Kenyan companies have to divert
their trading interests and partners to the Horn of Africa as "we
are facing stiff competition from South Africa in our traditional
markets of Uganda and Tanzania."
</P>
<P>
The release pointed out that Kenyan companies wishing to make
business contacts in the sub-region will benefit from the low
tariffs and political stability in Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
NBP Director Jeremiah Nyagah said he expected about 50 Kenyan
companies to participate in the exhibition which he said will
attract businessmen from Ethiopia, Yemen, Djibouti and Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
This is the first major trade fair to be held by Kenyan firms
in Ethiopia with a population of 52.8 million people.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the Network Business Promotion staged a "Kenya in
Uganda" exhibition where more than 50 Kenyan companies took part
and made business deals worth 22 million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
Recently, the same organizer staged a "Kenya in Tanzania" show
where Kenyan participants accrued orders worth about 37 million
Dollars. 
</P>
