<HEADLINE> China Prepares to Host World Gardening Expo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- China is busy preparing to host
the '99 World Gardening Expo, scheduled from May 31 to October 31
of 1999 in Kunming and believed to be the longest-running
international event in China,
</P>
<P>
Construction of exhibition halls is in the planning stages, and
delegations will soon be sent to other countries to solicit
participants for the world event, said Liu Jing, secretary-general
of the show's China organizational committee and vice governor of
Yunnan.
</P>
<P>
Kunming, the capital city of Yunnan Province, is known as a
"kingdom of plants."
</P>
<P>
Construction of the basic facilities is expected to be finished
by June of 1998, Liu said, adding that a number of infrastructure
projects, including road, airport and hotel construction and
expansion are being planned.  
</P>
