<HEADLINE> UN Passes Resolution on Nigerian Human Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Commission on
Human Rights has passed a resolution in Geneva criticizing
Nigeria's human rights situation, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
The reports said the resolution passed on Tuesday condemned
the "military authorities' arbitrary detentions" and the "flawed
judicial process" in Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
It also approved the appointment of a special investigator to
monitor human rights situation in Nigeria, the reports added.
</P>
<P>
The resolution was passed amid strong opposition from African
countries, many of which either abstained or voted against it,
said the reports. 
</P>
