<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading French newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- After six months of investigation, a commission of the
Belgian parliament in charge of investigating the Dutroux affair
has published its report, which presented evidence of dysfunction
of Belgium's judicial apparatus in its inquiry over disappearance
of children.
</P>
<P>
-- Up to 372 French soldiers participating in the "Operation
Alba" protection force in Albania arrived in the Albanian port of
Durres on Tuesday with all the quietness.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The 15 European Union countries proposed Tuesday at the
Euro-Mediterranean Conference in Malta that Palestinians and
Israelis take "reciprocal gestures" to "restore confidence"
between the two sides. They also tried to arrange a meeting
between Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat and Israeli Foreign
Minister David Levy.
</P>
<P>
-- At least 181 people died and more than 800 wounded as fire
broke out in the camps of Muslim pilgrims in Mina, near Mecca. A
gas bottle explosion was believed to be the cause of the fire,
which entirely overwhelmed the camps of pilgrims from India,
Pakistan, Malaysia and Indonesia and spread to Iranian and Arab
camps. 
</P>
