<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2 Hezbollah Fighters Killed in Israel's Swoop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Two guerrillas of the Lebanese
Hezbollah, or Party of God, were killed in the first clash with
Israeli forces in south Lebanon in a month, Beirut's press
reported Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
Israeli troops punched out of the occupied border strip Tuesday
morning to hunt down two Hezbollah fighters in a combat
reminiscent of Israel's grapes of wrath operation in April 1996
that claimed some 200 Lebanese lives, most of them civilians.
</P>
<P>
The daily Star, the only English daily in Beirut, said that
troops belonging to Israel's special force, known by their Hebrew
name of Egoz, thrust out of the so-called "security zone" and
raided the guerrillas at Wadi Froum some three kilometers north of
the demarcation line.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah admitted the losing of two fighters, Ali Ahmed Nazzal,
24, and Ahmed Mohammed Alayan, 20, in the pre-dawn battle, which
raged for more than 90 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Nazzal was buried in his hometown of Srifa and Alayan in
Qalawiyeh after midday prayers Tuesday, the report added.
</P>
<P>
A Hezbollah statement said there were casualties among the
Israelis, which Israel denied.
</P>
<P>
Voice of the South Radio, mouthpiece of the Israeli-backed
South Lebanon Army militia (SLA), quoted Major General Amiram
Levine, Israel's northern front commander, as congratulating the
soldiers "for a job well done."
</P>
<P>
He confirmed that the attackers were members of Egoz, the
special force whose main task is to track and hunt down resistance
fighters before they are able to penetrate the buffer zone.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah, which spearheads a guerrilla warfare in south
Lebanon to oust the Israeli occupation forces, has refrained from
pointing its barrel at the Israelis in nearly one month.
</P>
<P>
Fighting in recent weeks has pitted only the SLA, Israel's
client militia patrolling the buffer enclave, against the Lebanese
resistance militants.
</P>
<P>
In the last of three attacks since this month, a SLA militiaman
was killed and two others were wounded when Hezbollah fighters
detonated a roadside bomb near Teir Harfa on the edge of the
western sector of the zone last Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Israel established the 1,100-square-kilometer "security zone"
in 1985 to protect its northern border.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970416.0177 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-British Land Commission Agrees on Land Disposal Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese and British
sides on the Sino-British Land Commission reached agreement here
today on the land disposal program for the period from April 1 to
June 30 this year.
</P>
<P>
At the 34th meeting of the commission held this morning, the
two sides agreed that 98.76 hectares of land will be granted for
the last quarter before the handover.
</P>
<P>
The land comprises 8.15 hectares for commercial, residential
and industrial development, 4.45 hectares for the Private Sector
Participation Scheme, Hong Kong Housing Society development and
Village Housing, 1.42 hectares for public utilities, educational,
welfare, religious, recreational and other uses and 84.74 hectares
as special requirements.
</P>
<P>
At a press briefing after the meeting, Chen Rongchun, Chinese
senior representative to the commission, reassured that after the
establishment of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) government, all the assets of the HKSAR Government Land
Fund will be transferred to the HKSAR government.
</P>
<P>
The fund has been managed by trustees on the authorization of
China's central government, since its founding over 10 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-British Land Commission is also due to dissolve on
midnight June 30.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
