<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stock Market Rebounds by 230 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Hong Kong
Stock Exchange rebounded by 239 points today with the Hang Seng
Index (HSI) closing at 12,581.31, the highest of this month.
</P>
<P>
HSI's sub-indices also climbed today with finance jumping
209.52 points to 14,375.82, utilities rising 109.5 points to
10,528.79, properties rocketing 525.24 points to 21,929.2, and the
commercials and industrials up 194.20 points to 9,832.76.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index rose 16 points to 1,023
today.
</P>
<P>
The turnover reached 10.151 billion HK dollars (1.31 billion US
dollars), the highest of the trading days in April.
</P>
<P>
The stock analysts said the rebounding of the HSI which serves
as an indicator for blue chips on the local bourse represents the
potential growth of the Hong Kong Stock Exchange apart from the
growth of the share prices on the stock market in the United
States.
</P>
<P>
A broker said that today's climbing of the indices were mainly
promoted by the sub-index of the properties.
</P>
<P>
He said that properties index has been held back by various
factors within Hong Kong' market and overseas market, it is
nothing strange for the index to rebound today.
</P>
<P>
He said that he is still optimistic about the upward trend in
Hong Kong stock market in the coming weeks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
