<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Australian Parliamentarians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Vice-premier Zhu Rongji met today
with an Australian parliamentary delegation led by Bruce Reid,
chairman of the Australia-China Parliamentary Friendship Group.
</P>
<P>
"We place a great deal of importance on your visit," Zhu told
the parliamentarians, adding that he believes the visit will play
a role in deepening mutual understanding and advancing the two
countries' friendly and cooperative relations.
</P>
<P>
Zhu also briefed the guests on China's economic development and
progress in controlling environmental pollution.
</P>
<P>
Reid said the purpose of his China visit was to make more
friends and to look for new ways of cooperation in economy and
trade, with a view to contributing to the consolidation and
strengthening of the existing friendship between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Present at the meeting were Liu Huaqiu, director of the Foreign
Affairs Office of the State Council, and Liu Shuqing, President of
the Chinese People's Institute of Foreign Affairs.  
</P>
</TEXT>
