<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Another Foreign GSM Mobile Phone for China Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Hagenuk, the German GSM mobile
phone manufacturer, has entered the flourishing mobile
communications market in China, which has nearly doubled since the
GSM system was introduced in 1995.
</P>
<P>
To penetrate the China market, Hagenuk has designated the China
International Telecommunications Construction Corporation, the
Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications' largest telecoms
contractor, as the sole distributor for China's inland areas, Hong
Kong, and Macao.
</P>
<P>
The 100-year old Hagenuk manufactured the world's first
touch-tone, rotary, and cordless phones, and the digital mobile
phone with hidden antenna.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, more than 1,000 Chinese counties had access
to the global system for mobile communications (GSM). The number
of mobile phone customers in China is expected to reach 10 million
by the end of this year and 20 million by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Foreign mobile phone giants have been very active in the
world's largest emerging market, and at present nearly 100 percent
of the mobile phone market in China has been taken over by
overseas manufacturers or joint ventures with Nokia, Ericsson, and
Motorola. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
