<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fast Container Shipping Line Initiated Along China's Coast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Fast cargo container shipping
lines have been initiated between Shanghai, China's largest port,
and some other major coastal ports in the country.
</P>
<P>
The new lines were started this month between Shanghai and
Fujian and Guangdong provinces in east and south China, and will
soon be extended to some northern ports such as Yingkou, Tianjin
and Qingdao. The lines are operated by Shanghai Haixing Shipping
Co. Ltd.,
</P>
<P>
The speedier lines are expected to greatly improve container
shipping among China's coastal ports and some inland cities,
according to China Transportation News.
</P>
<P>
The shipping company uses high-speed all-container liners on
the new lines, and provides warehousing, loading and unloading of
containers, and sea-land through transport services.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Haixing Shipping Co. Ltd., a subsidiary of Shanghai
Ocean Shipping (Group) Co., is a leading coastal shipping company
in China with 185 ships in operation. The company is one of the
large state-owned enterprises listed in Hong Kong.  
</P>
