<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Peruvian Congress President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin met
here this morning with President of the Congress of Peru Victor
Joyway Rojas, calling him an "old friend of the Chinese people"
who has done much to assist the promotion of bilateral friendly
ties in the past years.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that Peru is an influential country in Latin
America, and since President Alberto Fujimori took office, it has
actively taken part in international and regional affairs,
continuously strengthened its relations with all the countries in
the world, and worked to promote the integration of Latin America.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, it has been highly successful in safeguarding
political stability, promoting economic development and improving
the livelihood of the Peruvian people, added Jiang, saying that
China is pleased at this and wishes that Peru can continue to make
new progress.
</P>
<P>
He said that Peru is one of the first countries in South
America to establish diplomatic relations with China, adding that
bilateral friendly cooperation in various fields has developed
substantially since the two countries forged diplomatic ties 25
years ago.
</P>
<P>
Exchanges of visits between leaders of the two parliaments and
governments have helped push forward the development of bilateral
friendship and cooperation, Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also asked Joyway to convey his regards to Fujimori.
</P>
<P>
Joyway said that he has witnessed China's remarkable economic
development in this visit, adding that he admires China's
outstanding progress in political, economic, social, cultural,
scientific and technological fields.
</P>
<P>
He said he is certain China will score even further
achievements in its national construction.
</P>
<P>
He said that Peru appreciates China's independent foreign
policy of peace, and his country is willing to continue to enhance
bilateral friendship and cooperation in various fields. 
</P>
