<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines will host the
Agriculture Asia '97 show and Postharvest Horticulture Asia '97
exhibition and conference on May 15-18, the Philippine News Agency
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Some 100 leading manufacturers, distributors and suppliers from
13 countries worldwide will attend the two events, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
David Chow, organizer of the shows, said Agriculture Asia '97
is the second of this biennial series shows which features a
comprehensive line-up technology and services in agriculture,
irrigation, animal husbandry and related agri-business industries.
</P>
<P>
Chow said that Postharvest Horticulture Asia '97 exhibition and
conference will address the specialized requirements and
specifications of the postharvest sector in terms of technology,
products and services.
</P>
<P>
He said the two events have gained unprecedented level of
industry support and participation following the recent robust
performance of the country's agriculture sector, contributing 20
percent of the total economy and the sector's output expanding by
3.7 percent in the first semester of this year.
</P>
<P>
Chow said for the first time Agriculture Asia show will feature
some outdoor exhibits to include a high-tech poultry house with
some 500 live chicken.
</P>
<P>
A high-level conference will also be held in line with the
Postharvest Horticulture Asia '97 from May 15 to 16 with theme
"Postharvest Systems Improvement towards Market Competitiveness,"
Chow said.  
