<HEADLINE> Agricultural Bank To Help The Poor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The Agricultural Bank of China
will set aside special loans totalling 400 million yuan (48.2
million US dollars) this year to support aid-the-poor projects in
six coastal provinces.
</P>
<P>
The effort will benefit Liaoning Province in northeast China,
south China's Guangdong Province, and the provinces of Jiangsu,
Fujian, Shandong, and Zhejiang in east China, according to China
Information.
</P>
<P>
This is an important measure in response to a national program
which started in 1994 to help 80 million people shake off poverty
within seven years, bank authorities note.
</P>
<P>
China's poverty-stricken population is now 58 million.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the bank has adopted various measures in terms
of credit, loan management, and the upgrading of financial
services to provide aid for poor regions, the authorities say.
</P>
