<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Products to Give Cleaner Air </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, April 16 (Xinhua) -- New products to control car
exhaust emission have been in wide use in northwest China's Gansu
Province as part of the local "Blue Sky Plan" to battle air
pollution.
</P>
<P>
There are now more than 80,000 vehicles in the area, which each
produced nearly 1,000 tons of exhaust per year.
</P>
<P>
A local company used new technology from Japan to develop two
kinds of systems to curb excess tailpipe emissions.
</P>
<P>
Inspections conducted by the provincial environmental
protection bureau show that the new products' purification rate of
carbon monoxide reached from 31 to 60 percent; that of
hydrocarbon, from 20 to 80 percent; and more than 80 percent for
diesel fumes.
</P>
<P>
The manufacturer said that new products could also help
vehicles to economize on gasoline, improve engine functioning and
reduce noise pollution caused by engines.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
