<HEADLINE> China's Freight Transport Volume Down in January, February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- China's freight transport volume
went down by 1.3 percent during the first two months of this year
compared with the corresponding 1996 period, standing at 423
million tons in total, according to the latest statistics from the
State Statistical Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The volume of rail freight was 255 million tons, down 2.3
percent from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
That of road haulage was 72 million tons, an increase of 1.7
percent.
</P>
<P>
That handled by freighters and barges stood at 96 million tons,
down 0.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The freight transport volume of civil aviation was 170,000
tons, up 5.4 percent. 
</P>
