<HEADLINE> China's Passenger Traffic Volume Up in January, February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- China's passenger traffic volume
reached 854 million persons during the first two months of this
year, up 3.6 percent form the same period of last year, according
to the latest statistics from the State Statistical Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The passenger traffic volume of railway was 150 million
persons, up 3.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
That of motor vehicles was 675 million persons, an increase of
3.8 percent over the corresponding 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
That of freighters and barges stood at 21 million persons, up
1.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The volume of civil aviation was 8.13 million persons, up four
percent. 
