<HEADLINE> China to Play Three Warm-ups for World Cup Qualifying </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese national soccer squad
will play three warm-ups to tune up for its World Cup qualifying
tournament slated in May.
</P>
<P>
China will play Myanmar on April 20, face South Korea on April
23 and meet Iran on April 27, the Chinese soccer association said
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar was rated out of the soccer powers in Asia, but bears
similarity with Vietnam in its soccer theory, which China will
meet in its group qualifying tournament.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Myanmar has whistled its footers to China's southern
city of Kunming to gear up for the East Asian Games to be kicked
off in Pusan, South Korea in early May.
</P>
<P>
South Korea will come over to meet China for the annual
Sino-Korea soccer matches which go to the second edition as both
sides are vying for a ticket for the 1998 World Cup finals in
France.
</P>
<P>
Iran ranked among the best in Asia, and even boasted a feat of
a 6-2 win over South Korea in the Asian Cup last year.
</P>
<P>
China had never played Iran after the Hiroshima Asian Games in
1994 when China routed Iran 1-0.
</P>
<P>
After the three warm-ups, the Chinese nationals will set off on
April 30 for their away games first against Turkmenistan and
Tajikistan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
