<HEADLINE> Gremio Beats Sporting Cristal in Libertadores Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's Gremio outscored Peru's
Sporting Cristal 2-0 in Porto Alegre Tuesday night, giving the
Brazilian squad the top spot in Group 4 of the Libertadores Cup
soccer tournament.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, the Peruvian team will have to face
Argentine power house Velez Sarsfield in the next round of play.
</P>
<P>
Gremio took the lead early when Paulo Nunes scored in the 9th
minute and Dauri sealed the game in the 37th minute for a 2-0
advantage which the hosts held till the end of the game.
</P>
<P>
Sporting Cristal prevented Gremio from scoring more in the
second half and couldn't put together themselves any plays to turn
back the loss. 
</P>
</TEXT>
