<HEADLINE> Prince Andrew Foresees More British Investment in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Visiting British Royal Prince
Andrew today told the business cycle in Harare that at least 10
prominent British companies are planning to increase investment
in Zimbabwe this year.
</P>
<P>
The Duke of York, who arrived in the Zimbabwean capital on
Tuesday, said the commercial links between Zimbabwe and Britain
were "very much alive and developing", disclosing that the new
British investment package may be worth 58.9 million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
Britain is the largest foreign investor in Zimbabwe with over
300 British companies owning around 515 million U.S. Dollars
worth of assets in the country.
</P>
<P>
Prince Andrew is on his first ever visit to Zimbabwe at the
invitation of Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe to attend the
final day of the peacekeeping exercise in the southern African
country.
</P>
<P>
The exercise, being held at a Zimbabwe National Army training
base, involves over 1,100 troops from eight Commonwealth member
countries from southern Africa and is the first multinational
peacekeeping exercise in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
