<HEADLINE> Tung Chee Hwa Not to Visit U.S. Before HK's Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 16 (Xinhua) -- A spokesman for the Chief
Executive's Office of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) confirmed here today that Tung Chee Hwa will not be making
a trip to the United States before the handover on July 1.
</P>
<P>
In response to press inquiries, the spokesman said that Tung,
Chief Executive, had made this decision mainly because of the
tremendous workload generated by the many pressing issues that
remained to be resolved.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Chief Executive believes his focus must be in
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Tung attached great importance to Hong Kong's relationship with
the United States and he would try to make the visit in the second
half of the year, the spokesman said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
