<HEADLINE> UN, Italy Confirm Humanitarian Assistance to Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations and Italian
leaders said today that the Italian-led multinational force to
Albania was providing humanitarian assistance rather than
disarming the Albanians.
</P>
<P>
After a meeting, UN Secretary-General Kofi Annan and Italian
Prime Minister Romano Prodi also confirmed the date for the Albanian
general elections as June 29.
</P>
<P>
Annan said the UN-approved 6,000-strong Operation Alba force
was to guarantee emergency food and medicine shipments to the
country.
</P>
<P>
Annan also rejected fears that the crisis in Albania might spread
into other countries in the Balkans.
</P>
<P>
Advance force had already arrived to make preparations for the
main force.
</P>
<P>
Annan thanked the countries sending soldiers to Albania,
including France, Spain, Greece, Turkey, Austria, Denmark and
Romania.
</P>
<P>
Prodi said it was "fundamental" to provide the Albanian people
with international assistance when "the government has been
reconstituted and the political system reinforced." 
</P>
</TEXT>
