<HEADLINE> Nepal's Tourism Benefits From Indian Films </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Many Indian films shot in Nepal
have played a vital role in promoting Nepal as a tourist
destination for Indian visitors, a leading businessman of Nepal's
tourism industry said.
</P>
<P>
Indian film makers who shoot their feature films in Nepal's
picturesque backdrops would also help make the Visit Nepal Year
1998 program a success, President of the Hotel Association of
Nepal (HAN) Yogendra Shakay said at a recent reception here.
</P>
<P>
The reception was organized by the HAN in honor of nearly 10
Indian film stars who were in Kathmandu for the inauguration of an
Indian Film Week beginning last Sunday.
</P>
<P>
There is a great relevance between India's film industry and
the hotel industry in Nepal, Shakay told the actors and actresses
from Mumbai, India's capital of film industry.
</P>
<P>
The publicity and promotion that Nepal could receive from
Indian films are immense as these films have a strong influence on
people in the South Asian region especially in India, he said,
adding that Indian visitors account for one-third of the total
tourist arrivals in Nepal.
</P>
<P>
Visit Nepal Year 1998, the tourism promotion program launched
by the government one year ago, is aimed at attracting 500,000
foreign tourists next year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
