<HEADLINE> Pakistani PM Hopes to Improve Pakistan-India Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif today expressed the hope to improve Pakistan-India ties
and settle the Kashmir issue peacefully and justly.
</P>
<P>
Making a speech titled "My Vision of Future Pakistan" at the
National Defense College here, Sharif said that he wants a
peaceful solution to the Kashmir problem in accordance with the
commitments made by the international community, India and
Pakistan to the Kashmiri people.
</P>
<P>
An equitable and just settlement of the Kashmir dispute, the
core issue between Pakistan and India, can guarantee peace in
South Asia, he said.
</P>
<P>
However, he noted, "We fully realize that there is no short cut
to the process of normalization of relations with India."
</P>
<P>
Pakistan and India restored the bilateral talks at the Foreign
Secretarial level by the end of March, which had been suspended
for three years.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister believed that an integrated structured
approach has to be pursued for co-operative and good neighborly
relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
