<DOCNO> XIE19970416.0246 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand to Standardize Economic Data System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's Finance Ministry will
speed up economic data gathering and reporting to maintain the
confidence of foreign investors and avoid mistakes in
macroeconomic management.
</P>
<P>
Chatu Mongol Sonakul, permanent secretary of the Finance
Ministry, said he had asked the Customs Department to report
import and export data within 10 days instead of 45 days, and the
Fiscal Policy Office to report gross domestic production every
three months rather than annually, according to the Nation today.
</P>
<P>
During a recent visit to Thailand, Michel Camdessus, managing
director of the International Monetary Fund, urged Thailand to
standardize its economic data system and said that the government
should quickly disseminate comprehensive and accurate information.
</P>
<P>
Reliable economic data would make it easier for the government
to deal with macroeconomic issues, while inaccurate information
from the government will send wrong signals which may cause the
private sector to fail to adjust to the changing economic
conditions, the IMF official said.
</P>
<P>
Camdessus told the Finance Ministry that Thailand's economic
data is messy. Government agencies give out different data even
though they obtain it from the same sources, according to Chatu.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970416.0247 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bus Hijacking Foiled in Southern Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Special police foiled a bus
hijacking in southern Russia Monday, rescuing 27 hostages and
capturing the hijacker.
</P>
<P>
The hijacker, a 25-year-old man from the Republic of Chechnya,
forced the bus driver and the passengers to go to the airport on
Monday afternoon in Makhachkala, capital of the southern Republic
of Dagestan.
</P>
<P>
The hijacker, armed with a grenade and automatic rifle,
demanded 100,000 U.S. dollars and a helicopter from the
authorities for his escape.
</P>
<P>
It took some 3 hours for the special police to end the
incident.
</P>
<P>
The Caucasus Mountains region has been troubled with
hostage-taking sprees in recent years, and Monday's episode was
one of the few that was resolved swiftly. 
</P>
