<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Tamil Rebels in Throes of Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The Liberation Tigers of Tamil
Eelam (LTTE), who has been fighting a 14-year guerrilla war for a
separate Tamil state, is reported to be in the throes of crisis
both militarily and politically, according to Tamil informed
sources today.
</P>
<P>
The crisis ranges from man power to logistics to being
increasingly rejected by the Tamil community not only in Colombo
but also in the North and the East where they hold very little
real estate now following major military reversals, the sources
said.
</P>
<P>
They pointed out that the LTTE lived a nomadic life in jungles
and was unable to conscript children and youth.
</P>
<P>
It was also experiencing difficulties in procuring arms and
ammunition as the rebel supply lines have been disrupted since the
government troops re-took Jaffna peninsula last May.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, they also face an acute shortage of medicine to
treat their wounded cadres, the sources added.  
</P>
