<HEADLINE> Bank Loans for Sri Lanka's Northern Farmers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Central Bank has
decided to grant loans to farmers in northern Jaffna peninsula in
an effort to reactivate the neglected agricultural sector there.
</P>
<P>
According to local newspaper reports today, agriculture has
been the main source of income for the majority of the people in
Northern and Eastern provinces. But following the 14-year ethnic
war agriculture in the areas has been totally disrupted.
</P>
<P>
The Jaffna peninsula was once the stronghold of the Tamil
rebels, who waged a guerrilla war for a separate state in the
north and east of the country.
</P>
<P>
Under the loan scheme each farmer will be given Rs 10,000
(about 170 US dollars). All farmers who have resettled in the
Jaffna peninsula will be eligible to apply for the loans.
</P>
<P>
The government has also made arrangements to supply seed,
chemicals and agricultural equipment required by the farming
community in the peninsula.  
