<HEADLINE> Hungary, Romania Agree to Improve Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Hungary and Romania have agreed
to conciliate their 1987 diplomatic dispute and improve their
relations, a spokesman at the Hungarian Foreign Ministry said
here today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman, Szentivanyi Ga'for, said that foreign ministries
of the two countries agreed to put aside the dispute and reopen in
the near future the general consulates in each other's countries,
which were closed after each country expelled a diplomatic
official of the other in 1987.
</P>
<P>
In November that year, Romania accused a Hungarian commercial
counsellor at the Hungarian embassy of carrying out activities
incompatible with his status and declared him as "persona non
grata." In retaliation, Hungary also expelled a counsellor of the
Romanian embassy in the country.
</P>
<P>
The agreement is seen here as a new step to improve relations
between the two countries after the new Romanian government came
into office in November last year. 
