<HEADLINE> Top Academy to Celebrate Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Social
Sciences will celebrate its 20th anniversary this May, and hopes
the event can be a means of improving public awareness of the
sector's importance.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the academy said that during the celebration
CASS will study urgent issues concerning the future of China's
research on philosophy, economics, and liberal arts.
</P>
<P>
The academy was previously a part of the Chinese Academy of
Sciences, and was given its current name in 1977. Since then, it
has evolved into an advisory body for the Chinese Communist Party
and the central government.
</P>
<P>
The academy has received increasing funding in recent years
from the central budget. Many Chinese leaders have given speeches
and communicated by letter to the institute, considered a hotbed
of new ideas.
</P>
<P>
The high-profile celebration will feature exhibitions, seminars
and other activities to reflect the academy's achievements in
stepping up the Chinese economy and social progress -- the current
focus of its 2,000 researchers.
</P>
<P>
Also in May, some foreigners will be given honorary titles as
senior researchers of the academy.
</P>
<P>
The academy, the leader in this field with a lot of young
scholars studying or working abroad, is a bridge to connect
Western culture and Chinese tradition.  
