<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Czech Republic, Norway Sign Gas Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The Czech Republic and Norway signed
an agreement on a gas supply here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Norway will provide the Czech Republic with 53
billion cubic meters of gas over the next 20 years. From May 1,
 Norway will supply 700 million cubic meters this year, seven
percent of the Czech gas consumption.
</P>
<P>
From the year 2002, Norway's annual gas supply to the Czech
Republic will be three billion cubic meters, and up to 2010 the
supply will be 22 percent of the Czech gas consumption.
</P>
<P>
With an annual gas consumption of 9.7 billion cubic meters at
present, the Czech Republic imports 8.5 billion cubic meters from Russia,
450 million cubic meters from Germany and 150 million cubic meters
from Ukraine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
