agriculture, and Israeli businessmen could help Ukraine in raising
chickens and growing vegetables and crops.
</P>
<P>
Lazarenko said the two countries could expand cooperation into
other sectors, including aviation and space. Ukrainian rockets
could send Israeli satellites into space, he added.
</P>
<P>
At present, there are 300,000 Ukrainian immigrants living in
Israel, serving as a bridge between the two countries. Sharansky
himself was born in Ukraine.  
