<HEADLINE> Brazil To Buy Electricity From Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The Brazilian government plans
to import 1,000 megawatts of electricity from Argentina to meet
the growing domestic demand, Mining and Energy Minister Raimundo
Brito said today.
</P>
<P>
In the first two months of this year, Brazil's power
consumption rose by 8.4 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Brazil will invest about 350 million U.S. dollars in a power
line for the transmission, which will connect the north, the south
and the central-west of the country.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the 1,270-kilometer line will cost 738
million dollars and Brazil will ask the Inter-American Development
Bank (IDB) to make up the shortfall, Brito said. 
</P>
