<HEADLINE> Italian Jet Fighter Crashes Into Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 15 (Xinhua) -- An Italian air force F-104 jet
fighter crashed into the Mediterranean sea during a training
flight today, and the fate of the pilot is unknown.
</P>
<P>
A military spokesman said the crash happened about 40 miles (64
kilometers) north of the island of Pantelleria, midway between
Sicily and the North Africa coast, during an exercise with two
other planes.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft lost contact with the other planes before plunging
into the sea, the spokesman was quoted as saying by the local
media.
</P>
<P>
Reports said helicopters had been sent to locate the pilot, but
so far only his helmet had been found.
</P>
<P>
"We have no information that the plane had any problems or any
confirmation that the pilot ejected," the spokesman said. He
added that an investigation was underway to determine the cause of
the crash. 
</P>
