<HEADLINE> IOC Backs World Youth Games in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Moscow has won the backing of the
International Olympic Committee for its hosting of the first
"World Youth Games" slated in July 1998.
</P>
<P>
An agreement of patronage was signed among the IOC, the city of
Moscow and the Russian Olympic Committee in Lausanne, sources said
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
IOC president Juan Antonio Samaranch gave his support to the
games in a meeting with Moscow Mayor Yuri Luzhkov who will act as
president of the organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
The youth games scheduled for July 11-19, come as a consolation
to Russia after St. Petersburg was circled out among six cities in
their bids for the 2004 Summer Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Russian officials said 68 countries have confirmed their
participation in the event so far. 
</P>
