<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Ros Herreros scored 19 points and
Josef Arlauckas added 18 as Real Madrid won the Eurocup basketball
title by beating Riello Verona 78-64 in Nicosia, Italy, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Real Madrid dominated the game almost from the start and the
Italian team could get no closer than eight points in the final 15
minutes.
</P>
<P>
The Spanish team opened a 9-0 lead in the game's first four
minutes with Herreros scoring five quick points.
</P>
<P>
Verona took the lead briefly at 18-17 with just over seven
minutes left in the first half.
</P>
<P>
But nine points by Herreros over the next three minutes put
Real Madrid back in control and they led 36-30 at half time.
</P>
<P>
They stretched their advantage to 58-44 midway through the
second half. 
