<HEADLINE> Makinen Shares Lead with Liatti </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, April 15 (Xinhua) -- World champion Tommi Makinen of
Finland shared the lead with Italian Piero Liatti after the second
day of the Catalonia Rally in LLoret De Mar on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
With his Mitsubishi, Makinen, who went into the round in third
place, finished with an overall time of 3 hours 3 minutes and 56
seconds.
</P>
<P>
Liatti, on the Subaru team, clocked the same time in the
overall standings.
</P>
<P>
Another Subaru driver Scotland's Colin McRae dropped from first
place to No. 4 after finishing 3 minutes 32 seconds behind. McRae
and Liatti were winner and runnerup in last year's Catalonia Rally.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, French driver Gilles Panizzi, on the Peugeot team,
edged up to No. 3 from No. 9 Monday after coming in at 2:30 behind
Makinen and Liatti.
</P>
<P>
The rally, which finishes Wednesday, is the fifth of the World
Rally season and the first to be held on pure tarmac. 
</P>
