<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Dollar Falls in New York </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. dollar fell today after
hitting its second straight 38-month high against the mark.
</P>
<P>
In intraday dealings, the dollar reached a high of 1.7374
marks, the strongest since February 1994 and the second
consecutive 38-month high, before retreating to settle at 1.7270
in New York, down from 1.7298 Monday. The dollar settled at 126.09
yen, down from 126.20.
</P>
<P>
The pound rose sharply to 1.6316 dollars, up from 1.6210.
</P>
<P>
The dollar began to fall against the mark after the Commerce
Department reported lower-than-expected consumer inflation data
for March, which diminished the prospects that the Federal Reserve
may raise interest rates again at its next policymaking committee
meeting in May.
</P>
<P>
Other late dollar rates in New York compared with Friday: 1.4665
Swiss francs, down from 1.4705; 5.8085 French francs, down from
5.8155; 1,699.25 Italian lire, down from 1,700.75; 1.3965 Canadian
dollars, down from 1.3992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
