<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Jones Industrial Average Rallies Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial average
bounced back again today after interest rates eased from a
nine-month high in the bond market following a surprisingly tame
inflation report.
</P>
<P>
Technology shares slumped, however, following a discouraging
outlook issued by Intel with an otherwise impressive earnings
report.
</P>
<P>
The Dow rose 135.26 points to 6,587.16, after a gain of 60
points Monday.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 12-to-5 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with NYSE volume reaching 506.85
million shares, higher than 406.79 million in the previous
session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 10.99 to 754.72, the
NYSE's composite index rose 6.13 to 397.62, and the American Stock
Exchange composite index rose 2.09 to 555.06.
</P>
<P>
Under the pressure of declining technology shares, the Nasdaq
composite index fell 3.65 to 1,212.76. 
</P>
</TEXT>
